rComments: I took her "Cook the Books" class and it was the best course I've ever taken! She is a generous grader and her essays are often informal. The readings and lectures were always engaging. Only thing is, you MUST attend class. Otherwise you'll be lost, and also miss out on a lot of delicious food.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Extremely passionate. Lectures were relaxed and interactive. Gives good feedback on assignments. Lovely person altogether - I had a lot of fun in her course.

Andrea Most is one of the best profs I've ever had.  I went on to get my PhD in English and she greatly influenced me in my second year at U of T.  Amazing prof!!!!  Clear, original, fair, inspiring, kind.

Professor Most is a fabulous lecturer and is incredibly intelligent. She engages students and makes an effort to get to know people who participate. I loved her reading list and she challenged me to think about literature in a deeper and more meaningful way. She is a tough marker but is always available to talk about essays. I highly recommend her!

She was a great lecturer. However, she was a VERY HARD marker who has unrealistic expectations of what a student can accomplish in a course when they are carrying a full course load. Although she made her class interesting, it was overshadowed by the stress I went through trying to achieve an ok grade. wouldn't take a class with her again!!!

Brilliant, contemporary in her interests and research, encourages and moderates discussions so they're stimulating, and she's a tough marker who rewards effort.  People who think you need to regurgitate her lectures for high marks are so far off the mark it's laughable.  I recommend her all the time.

I agree with an earlier poster than she tends to pick favourites. As a non-Jewish student, I felt sometimes uncomfortable b/c I was the minority, but had obvious interest. She's a difficult marker unless you restate her own thoughts. It's hard to go out on your own unless it's similar to her opinions. She is very nice though.

Has a gift with words which makes her a talented communicator both in class and out. To say she is a "ditz" is humorous; Out of 100 people, she would rank in the first percentile of intelligence! in fact, the downside to her intelligence, is that the class discussion is quite intense, not casual. I left class smarter, just by hearing her think.

[Disclaimer: this was the first university English class I took, and I only audited it.] Prof. Most lectured insightfully, conveying a lot of information in short periods, and ran good class discussions. She knows her contemporary drama, which gives her authority without making her overbearing.

more a jewish studies class than an english course.  great book list and lectures but its all about her - might as well leave your thoughts at home, she's not interested. seems to only be into her own opinions - grades according to how well you regurgetate her thoughts.  very energetic/nice but...

Not Jewish? Don't take it.  Great course material but she her comments merely graze the surface, nothing is ever explored in any great depth beyond my meagre knowledge.  Often was made to feel very uncomfortable in the class.

Great prof!  Knows her stuff - very intelligent.  I would take another class from her if she wasn't taking a year off to write another book.  I was not interested in Jewish lit at all, it was the only class I could get into, but I stayed with it after her first stimulating lecture!  Well done!

Good prof, good selection of course materials, well-researched lectures. Engages students. Tends to slant things overmuch in direc. of own research. Lots of discussion in class but usually seems to be humouring students w.out being interested. Overall recommend her. Class where you get what you give
agree with the ditz comment. spent too much time on broadway musicals. sometimes fairly shallow treatments of texts and topics. but performing groups were fun.
she good

Bit of a ditz.  Surely there is more to American Studies than this team taught course.  Not what I expected.  m-i-c-k-e-y.....
Hard marker. Picks favourites. Snobby. She's nothing special as a prof. Great booklist.
Uses films, current examples, and she's totally helpful.  She IS swell.
Seems kind. Engaged with the material.  Hip readings.  Encourages discussion.  Willing to help.  Lectures aren't mind-blowers, but they're solid.  Has a certain sexy vibe
She's just swell!
